LOCUS       AB384297                2360 bp    DNA     linear   SYN 26-JUL-2016
DEFINITION  Synthetic construct DNA, clone: pF1KSDA1809, Homo sapiens BCL11A
            gene for B-cell lymphoma/leukemia 11A, complete cds, without stop
            codon, in Flexi system.
ACCESSION   AB384297
VERSION     AB384297.1
KEYWORDS    Flexi cloning system; full-length ORF without stop codon.
SOURCE      synthetic construct
  ORGANISM  synthetic construct
            other sequences; artificial sequences.
REFERENCE   1
  AUTHORS   Nagase,T., Yamakawa,H., Tadokoro,S., Nakajima,D., Inoue,S.,
            Yamaguchi,K., Itokawa,Y., Kikuno,R.F., Koga,H. and Ohara,O.
  TITLE     Exploration of human ORFeome: high-throughput preparation of ORF
            clones and efficient characterization of their protein products
  JOURNAL   DNA Res. 15 (3), 137-149 (2008)
   PUBMED   18316326
REFERENCE   2  (bases 1 to 2360)
  AUTHORS   Nagase,T., Yamakawa,H., Kikuno,R.F. and Ohara,O.
  TITLE     Direct Submission
  JOURNAL   Submitted (15-FEB-2008) Contact:Takahiro Nagase Kazusa DNA Research
            Institute, Huamn Genome Research; Kazusa-Kamatari 2-6-7, Kisarazu,
            Chiba 292-0818, Japan
COMMENT     This clone is part of the Kazusa ORFeome Project. The ORF sequence
            was derived from a pENT clone, which was constructed by the ORF
            trap cloning method based on a homologous recombination in E. coli
            using a cloned cDNA (DNA Res. 12, 257-267, 2005) and subcloned into
            a pF1K-based vector using restriction enzymes.
            Please visit our website.
            URL: http://www.kazusa.or.jp/kop.
